The Music Society of Makhanda is set to hold two thrilling performances this month, with organist Louri Coetzee taking to the stage on 11 February and a piano duet by Spina and Benignetti on 24 February.“2022 was a fulfilling year for the Music Society of Makhanda, in terms of the high standard of all performances, interesting variety in the works performed and good-sized and enthusiastic audiences. 2023 promises to be at least as good” says the society’s co-ordinator John Jackson. The society will also hold its Annual General Meeting on Thursday 9 February at 5:30pm in the St. Andrew’s College Staff Room.